{"TopicId":153533,"ForumId":20,"TopicTitle":"What is MechJeb and what does it do?","CreatedByName":"Jeb!","CreatedById":159364,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-14T21:24:51Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Jeb!","CreatedById":159364,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-14T21:24:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHello\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m fairly new to modding in KSP. I\u0027ve seen that a lot of people use MechJeb, and some see it as an essential mod for\u00A0their install.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t really know much about it,\u00A0could someone explain to me what MechJeb is, what it does, and why I should (or shouldn\u0027t) use it?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks!\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:cool:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cool.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:cool:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gaarst","CreatedById":126740,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-14T21:28:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGives you all sorts of information that, IMO, we\u0027d need to have in the stock game, as well as an autopilot for sending stuff in orbit and docking. Probably also does a bunch of other things.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you don\u0027t want to use\u00A0an autopilot and want to do everything on your own, then \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Mechjeb (mod)\u0022\u003EMJ\u003C/abbr\u003E is pretty much equivalent to any other information mod (\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Engineer Redux (mod)\u0022\u003EKER\u003C/abbr\u003E, VOID...). There are a couple other autopilots mods out there, but I\u0027d say \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Mechjeb (mod)\u0022\u003EMJ\u003C/abbr\u003E is the most advanced.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jeb!","CreatedById":159364,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-14T23:55:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222887918\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022153533\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221481750931\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022126740\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Gaarst\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, Gaarst said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGives you all sorts of information that, IMO, we\u0027d need to have in the stock game, as well as an autopilot for sending stuff in orbit and docking. Probably also does a bunch of other things.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you don\u0027t want to use\u00A0an autopilot and want to do everything on your own, then \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Mechjeb (mod)\u0022\u003EMJ\u003C/abbr\u003E is pretty much equivalent to any other information mod (\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Engineer Redux (mod)\u0022\u003EKER\u003C/abbr\u003E, VOID...). There are a couple other autopilots mods out there, but I\u0027d say \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Mechjeb (mod)\u0022\u003EMJ\u003C/abbr\u003E is the most advanced.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThank you for your reply!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat sort of information does it provide specifically? How does the autopilot work, and can it complete entire missions from takeoff to landing by itself, or do you have to train it somehow?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-12-14T23:56:30Z\u0022 title=\u002212/14/2016 11:56  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 14, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Jeb!\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"legoclone09","CreatedById":142607,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-15T00:28:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222888087\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022153533\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221481759740\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022159364\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Jeb!\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n31 minutes ago, Jeb! said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThank you for your reply!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat sort of information does it provide specifically? How does the autopilot work, and can it complete entire missions from takeoff to landing by itself, or do you have to train it somehow?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt gives you Delta-V, \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Thrust-to-weight ratio\u0022\u003ETWR\u003C/abbr\u003E, orbital details, target details, etc. It can complete entire missions for you, it can do liftoff, maneuvers, and I believe landing. You don\u0027t need to train it. Very useful, but if you don\u0027t want the autopilot you can install Kerbal Engineer for just the ship stats.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jeb!","CreatedById":159364,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-15T00:30:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222888118\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022153533\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221481761700\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022142607\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022legoclone09\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, legoclone09 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt gives you Delta-V, \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Thrust-to-weight ratio\u0022\u003ETWR\u003C/abbr\u003E, orbital details, target details, etc. It can complete entire missions for you, it can do liftoff, maneuvers, and I believe landing. You don\u0027t need to train it. Very useful, but if you don\u0027t want the autopilot you can install Kerbal Engineer for just the ship stats.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThank you! MechJeb sounds like a really useful mod. I think I will start using next time I rebuild my install.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:cool:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cool.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:cool:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"legoclone09","CreatedById":142607,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-15T00:33:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222888120\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022153533\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221481761825\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022159364\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Jeb!\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 minutes ago, Jeb! said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThank you! MechJeb sounds like a really useful mod. I think I will start using next time I rebuild my install.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:cool:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cool.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:cool:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nVery useful, and I love it!\u003Cbr\u003E\nAnd this see